Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
define_add_on_module_model(25.10)            define_add_on_module_model(25.10)

Name
       define_add_on_module_model  -  Allows you to define the add_on types or
       supplemental models that can be loaded additionally  with  an  existing
       model or a design

Syntax
       define_add_on_module_model

       [-help]

       [-commit_callback <string>]

       -type <string >

       {[-create_callback <string>]

       [-set_callback <string>]

       [-restore_callback <string>]

       [-write_context_callback <string>]}

       Allows  you  to define the add_on types or supplemental models that can
       be loaded additionally with an existing model or a design. These  user-
       defined add_on types can be used with the create_module_model, set_mod-
       ule_model,  restore_module_model,  and  write_module_model_context com-
       mands. You must provide a TCL file containing callback  procedures  for
       each  applicable  Integrated  Hierarchical Database (iHDB) flow command
       that will be run when this command is called.

       In the TCL file, the TCL callback procedures must  be  defined  in  the
       following format and must include the specified arguments:

       <proc <callBackTCLProcName> {dir cell tag args} {...}>

       Where,

       dir,  cell, and tag represent values that will be automatically derived
       by the iHDB capability.

       args can be set using  set_module_model  -default_commit_options  {<op-
       tions>} -type <add_ons_type>

Parameters
       -commit_callback <string>
              Specifies  the  user-defined TCL procedure that is executed when
              the commit_module_model command  is  called  with  this  add_ons
              type.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -create_callback <string>
              Specifies  the  user-defined TCL procedure that is executed when
              the create_module_model command  is  called  with  this  add_ons
              type.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each define_add_on_module_model parameter. For a
              detailed description of the command and all of  its  parameters,
              use the man command:

              man define_add_on_module_model

       -restore_callback <string>
              Specifies  the  user-defined TCL procedure that is executed when
              the restore_module_model command is  called  with  this  add_ons
              type.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -set_callback <string>
              Specifies  the  user-defined TCL procedure that is executed when
              the set_module_model command is called with this add_ons type.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -type <string >
              Specifies the newly added add_ons model type name.

              Data_type: string, required

              -write_context_callback <string>" Specifies the user-defined TCL
              procedure that is executed when  the  write_module_model_context
              command is called with this add_ons type.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              *

                Following  is an example of defining the "attrs" add_ons model
                type. First this 'attrs' attribute must be  defined  with  the
                define_add_on_module_model  command  with its associated call-
                back TCL procedures:

                source dump_attrs.tcl

                set_module_model  -default_commit_options   {-keepPinGeometry}
                -type pnr

                define_add_on_module_model    -type   attrs   -create_callback
                ihdb_create_attrs -set_callback ihdb_read_attrs

                Where dump_attrs.tcl contains:

                proc ihdb_create_attrs {dir cell tag args} {    ;#This  format
                is fixed

                  write_block_attrs $dir/$cell/$tag/attrs/db.attrs

                }

                proc  ihdb_read_attrs {dir cell tag args} {  ;# This format is
                fixed

                  read_block_attrs $dir/$cell/$tag/attrs/db.attrs

                }

                ...

              * Block Level. The following command creates user defined  attrs
                type of module model that has the merge_attribute tag.

                create_module_model -type attrs -tag merge_attribute

                create_module_model -tag merge_attribute

              * Top-Level.  The  following commands configures and commits the
                merge_attribute module model using the attrs add-on associated
                with the pnr model type:

                set_module_model -cell  dcm  -tag  merge_attribute  -type  pnr
                -add_ons {attrs}

                set_module_model  -cell  lsu  -tag  merge_attribute  -type pnr
                -add_ons {attrs}

                commit_module_model

